Set statusled on STM32.
For use in vdr-plugin-statusleds.

Usage:
stm32kbdIRstatusled [-d device] -s led_state

Examples:
switch the statusled on:  stm32kbdIRstatusled -d /dev/hidraw1 -s 1
switch the statusled off: stm32kbdIRstatusled -d /dev/hidraw1 -s 0

put the udev rule from irmplircd into your udev rules directory, then you don't need to give a device

vdr + vdr-plugin-statusleds + stm32kbdIRstatusled:
vdr -P'statusleds --stm32kbdIRstatusled_path=/path/to/stm32kbdIRstatusled'
this will turn the led on, when vdr starts; it will turn the led off, when vdr stops; it will make the led blink during recording
for systemd add a line to the vdr service ExecStop=/path/to/stm32kbdIRstatusled -s 0
